First, let's recall ***what is the exchange ratio?***

The exchange ratio only exists in deals that are paid for in stock or a mix of stock and cash as opposed to just cash. It expresses how many shares an acquiring company needs to issue for each share an investor owns in a target company to provide its relative value. 

The calculation for the exchange ratio can be performed by dividing the target share price by the acquirer share price:
$$
\begin{equation}
\text{Exchange ratio} = \frac{\text{Target share price}}{\text{Acquirer share price}} 
\end{equation}
$$
